public class LevelManager
extends GameManager
LevelManager class as game manager to take charge of loading, arranging levels and sets of levels for user to choose and play.

    • loadSet

      public void loadSet​(java.io.InputStream input, java.lang.String setName)
      Loads, decodes and saves all levels of a given set inputStream from resource file.
      When a level is down decoding, a new level object is instantiated and add to set list.
      This method will be called when user intends to choose a set of levels or start the new game.
      Parameters:
      input - InputStream specifying the input as set of levels to read from.
      setName - String value specifying the name of set to be loaded.
      See Also:
      Level, m_CurrentSet, LevelSetScreenController, StartScreenController

    • nextLevel

      public Level nextLevel()
      Gets the next level from current set.
      Returns:
      If there exists a next level, then Level object is returned to caller; Otherwise, GameEngine is then requested to show Victory Screen to inform to user the completion of the current set, null is returned.
      See Also:
      GameEngine.toVictoryScreen()
